![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/efd52aef-1ba8-4b4f-9ba4-3d0648ca1c02/ep380.jpg?format=original)

With Marvel’s _Thunderbolts_ film on the horizon, the Major Issues Podcast crew dives headfirst into the original 1997 _Thunderbolts Vol. 1_ comic series by Kurt Busiek and Mark Bagley! In this episode, we explore the jaw-dropping twist that redefined villainy in the Marvel Universe, discuss how this bold concept flipped expectations, and break down why this run still resonates nearly three decades later. Whether you’re a longtime fan or brand new to the team, this is the perfect primer to understand the comic book roots of Marvel’s most unpredictable squad before they hit the big screen! Strap in as we talk Zemo, Citizen V, and one of the best bait-and-switch moments in Marvel history!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

